                <div class="about-section">
                    <h3>The Project</h3>
                    <p>
                        I built this dashboard to provide a real-time view of system's vital statistics. My goal was to create a clean, modern, and accessible monitoring tool using Node.js to gather system data and WebSockets to push that information instantly to the UI. I developed the application iteratively, focusing on creating a robust architecture and a great user experience.
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="about-section">
                    <h3>Key Features</h3>
                    <ul class="tech-list">
                        <li class="tech-item">Real-time CPU, Memory, Swap, and Disk monitoring</li>
                        <li class="tech-item">Live network usage chart (Upload/Download)</li>
                        <li class="tech-item">Light & Dark theme support</li>
                        <li class="tech-item">Selectable data refresh interval (1s, 2s, 5s)</li>
                        <li class="tech-item">Detailed system and hardware information</li>
                        <li class="tech-item">Cross-platform compatibility (macOS, Windows, Linux)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="about-section">
